Beech Hill Advisors Inc. Has $362,000 Position in Avon Products, Inc. (AVP)

					Posted by Jesse Mackey on Jul 19th, 2017 // No Comments 



Beech Hill Advisors Inc. increased its position in shares of  Avon Products, Inc. (NYSE:AVP) by 9.8% during the second quarter, Holdings Channel reports. The firm owned 95,300 shares of the company’s stock after buying an additional 8,500 shares during the period. Beech Hill Advisors Inc.’s holdings in Avon Products were worth $362,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
Other large investors also recently added to or reduced their stakes in the company. Americafirst Capital Management LLC acquired a new stake in shares of  Avon Products during the first quarter valued at approximately $689,000.  Parametrica Management Ltd raised its stake in shares of  Avon Products by 119.7% in the first quarter. Parametrica Management Ltd now owns 29,338 shares of the company’s stock valued at $129,000 after buying an additional 15,985 shares during the last quarter.  Capstone Asset Management Co. raised its stake in shares of  Avon Products by 1.5% in the first quarter. Capstone Asset Management Co. now owns 38,157 shares of the company’s stock valued at $168,000 after buying an additional 560 shares during the last quarter.  Highbridge Capital Management LLC acquired a new stake in shares of  Avon Products during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $335,000.  Finally, Teachers Advisors LLC raised its stake in shares of  Avon Products by 223.7% in the fourth quarter. Teachers Advisors LLC now owns 2,273,528 shares of the company’s stock valued at $11,459,000 after buying an additional 1,571,089 shares during the last quarter. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own  86.90% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Avon Products Inc. alerts:



Avon Products, Inc. (NYSE AVP) traded up 1.96% during trading on Wednesday, hitting $3.65. The stock had a trading volume of 617,226 shares. The company’s market capitalization is $1.61 billion. The stock’s 50-day moving average price is $3.60 and its 200-day moving average price is $4.38. Avon Products, Inc. has a 1-year low of $3.24 and a 1-year high of $6.96. 




Avon Products (NYSE:AVP) last announced its earnings results on Thursday, May 4th. The company reported ($0.07) earnings per share for the quarter, missing analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.01 by $0.08. The company had revenue of $1.33 billion for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $1.33 billion. Avon Products had a net margin of 0.26% and a negative return on equity of 3.68%. Avon Products’s quarterly revenue was up 2.0% on a year-over-year basis. During the same quarter in the prior year, the firm posted ($0.07) earnings per share.  Analysts expect that  Avon Products, Inc. will post $0.22 earnings per share for the current year. 
