Frequently Asked Questions for Avon Products (NYSE:AVP)
What is Avon Products' stock symbol?

Avon Products trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "AVP."



How were Avon Products' earnings last quarter?

Avon Products, Inc. (NYSE:AVP) issued its quarterly earnings data on Thursday, May, 4th. The company reported ($0.07) earnings per share for the quarter, missing the consensus estimate of $0.01 by $0.08. The business earned $1.33 billion during the quarter, compared to analysts' expectations of $1.33 billion. Avon Products had a negative return on equity of 3.68% and a net margin of 0.26%. The company's revenue was up 2.0% on a year-over-year basis. During the same quarter in the previous year, the company posted ($0.07) earnings per share.  View Avon Products' Earnings History.



When will Avon Products make its next earnings announcement?

Avon Products is scheduled to release their next quarterly earnings announcement on Thursday, August, 3rd 2017. View Earnings Estimates for Avon Products.



Where is Avon Products' stock going? Where will Avon Products' stock price be in 2017?

5 brokerages have issued twelve-month price targets for Avon Products' stock. Their predictions range from $4.00 to $8.00. On average, they anticipate Avon Products' stock price to reach $5.90 in the next year. View Analyst Ratings for Avon Products.



Who are some of Avon Products' key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Avon Products include Tupperware Brands Corporation (TUP), John Wiley & Sons (JW.A), New York Times Company (The) (NYT), 51job (JOBS), Energizer Holdings (ENR), Sanderson Farms (SAFM), Vector Group (VGR), Darling Ingredients (DAR), Helen of Troy Limited (HELE), Ollie's Bargain Outlet Holdings (OLLI), Meredith Corporation (MDP), Nomad Foods Limited (NOMD), Fresh Del Monte Produce (FDP), Britvic PLC Sponsored ADR (BTVCY), B&G Foods (BGS), J & J Snack Foods Corp. (JJSF), Hillenbrand (HI) and Coca-Cola Bottling Co. Consolidated (COKE).



Who are Avon Products' key executives?

Avon Products' management team includes the folowing people: Sherilyn S. McCoy, Chief Executive Officer, DirectorJames Wilson, Chief Financial Officer, Executive Vice PresidentJames S. Scully, Chief Operating Officer, Executive Vice PresidentSusan Ormiston, Senior Vice President - Human Resources, Chief Human Resources OfficerFernando J. Acosta, Executive Vice President, Chief Marketing and Social Selling OfficerJohn P. Higson, Executive Vice President, Chief Commercial OfficerJeff Benjamin, Senior Vice President, Chief Ethics & Compliance Officer, General CounselRobert Loughran, Group Vice President, Chief Accounting OfficerChan W. Galbato, Non-Executive Chairman of the BoardW. Don Cornwell, Lead Independent Director



Who owns Avon Products stock?

Avon Products' stock is owned by a variety of of retail and institutional investors. Top institutional investors include Shah Capital Management (0.94%), Prescott Group Capital Management L.L.C. (0.10%), State Treasurer State of Michigan (0.04%), Aperio Group LLC (0.04%), Russell Investments Group Ltd. (0.04%) and Municipal Employees Retirement System of Michigan (0.04%). Company insiders that own Avon Products stock include Fernando Acosta, James S Scully, John Higson, Jose Armario and W Don Cornwell. View Institutional Ownership Trends for Avon Products.



Who sold Avon Products stock? Who is selling Avon Products stock?

Avon Products' stock was sold by a variety of institutional investors in the last quarter, including Russell Investments Group Ltd., Prescott Group Capital Management L.L.C., Aperio Group LLC, Municipal Employees Retirement System of Michigan, Marshwinds Advisory Co. and Capstone Asset Management Co..  View Insider Buying and Selling for Avon Products.



Who bought Avon Products stock? Who is buying Avon Products stock?

Avon Products' stock was acquired by a variety of institutional investors in the last quarter, including Shah Capital Management, Parametrica Management Ltd, ING Groep NV, Beech Hill Advisors Inc., Oregon Public Employees Retirement Fund, LS Investment Advisors LLC, Louisiana State Employees Retirement System and State Treasurer State of Michigan. Company insiders that have bought Avon Products stock in the last two years include James S Scully, John Higson, Jose Armario and W Don Cornwell. View Insider Buying and Selling for Avon Products.



How do I buy Avon Products stock? 

Shares of Avon Products can be purchased through any online brokerage account. Popular online brokerages include Vanguard Brokerage Services, TD Ameritrade, E*TRADE, Scottrade, Fidelity and Charles Schwab. 



What is Avon Products' stock price today?

One share of Avon Products stock can currently be purchased for approximately $3.70.


